WEBVTT

00:07.224 --> 00:10.227
Think after several decades
you'd be just a little
bit better at this.

00:10.271 --> 00:11.141
No![Bottle shatters]

00:11.185 --> 00:12.577
We're banned for life.

00:12.621 --> 00:14.144
This whole thing is weird
and stupid.

00:14.188 --> 00:16.233
You really don't need
to worry about that anymore.

00:16.277 --> 00:17.147
[Door closes]

00:17.191 --> 00:18.670
You remember
my partner Bram?

00:18.714 --> 00:21.021
He asked me to plant evidence
for him once.

00:21.064 --> 00:22.587
And everybody knew.

00:22.631 --> 00:24.459
This is Patti at a gas station
in Vermont.

00:24.502 --> 00:26.504
I know she's wrapped up
in something bad.

00:26.548 --> 00:27.679
Sam, I don't want to leave.

00:27.723 --> 00:29.855
Sam: What?
Your great life here?

00:29.899 --> 00:31.509
Yeah.
I mean, Tammy --

00:31.553 --> 00:32.945
She is a problem.

00:32.989 --> 00:35.165
But now I know how to take
care of my problems.

00:35.209 --> 00:36.906
I introduce them
to Kevin.

00:40.127 --> 00:42.259
[Lively conversations]

00:42.303 --> 00:44.696
[Rock music playing softly]

00:44.740 --> 00:47.482
♪

00:47.525 --> 00:53.923
♪ It came so easily,
I let it follow me right down ♪

00:53.966 --> 00:56.621
♪ Crept in close
without a sound ♪

00:56.665 --> 00:58.188
[Grunts]
[Yelps]

00:58.232 --> 01:01.104
♪

01:01.148 --> 01:02.192
[Grunts]

01:02.236 --> 01:04.934
♪

01:04.977 --> 01:07.458
You tried
to kill Kevin.

01:07.502 --> 01:14.552
♪

01:14.596 --> 01:16.076
[Pool balls clatter]

01:16.119 --> 01:21.516
♪

01:21.559 --> 01:27.087
♪

01:27.130 --> 01:28.131
Hey.

01:28.175 --> 01:31.265
♪

01:31.308 --> 01:33.310
You wanna hear
a crazy story?

01:33.354 --> 01:34.746
♪

01:34.790 --> 01:37.009
[ Laughter]

01:37.053 --> 01:39.882
[High-pitched ringing]

01:39.925 --> 01:42.102
♪

01:45.801 --> 01:48.499
[Teeth brushing in distance]

01:48.543 --> 01:59.728
♪

01:59.771 --> 02:02.600
Hey, Kev,
I forgot to tell you -- I, um --

02:02.644 --> 02:05.560
I talked to Tammy about that
fire that caused the blackout.

02:05.603 --> 02:07.997
And she agreed with me
and said it looked suspicious

02:08.040 --> 02:09.564
and that she'd look into it.

02:12.523 --> 02:15.787
Tammy said arsonists can do
some pretty serious prison time.

02:15.831 --> 02:18.529
Don't you feel safer now
that she's on the case?

02:18.573 --> 02:20.792
No.
No, not at all.

02:20.836 --> 02:22.011
[ Laughter]

02:22.054 --> 02:23.360
Uh...

02:23.404 --> 02:24.492
uh...

02:24.535 --> 02:25.710
Ah.

02:25.754 --> 02:26.972
[Swallows]

02:27.016 --> 02:28.365
[ Laughter]

02:28.409 --> 02:31.151
Babe, I've got a confession
to make.

02:31.194 --> 02:35.024
And I think
you should sit down.

02:35.067 --> 02:37.374
I'm lying down.

02:37.418 --> 02:39.811
Right. Uh, guess
I should lie down, too.

02:39.855 --> 02:42.814
[Chuckles nervously]
Um...

02:42.858 --> 02:45.121
I started that fire.

02:46.253 --> 02:47.819
What?

02:47.863 --> 02:49.386
What fire?

02:49.430 --> 02:51.997
Not -- Not the one
that caused the blackout.

02:52.041 --> 02:54.304
Yeah. That fire.

02:54.348 --> 02:56.437
I also started two other
pretty big ones,

02:56.480 --> 02:58.874
but that's the main one
for this conversation.

02:58.917 --> 03:01.181
Oh, this is not good.

03:01.224 --> 03:03.748
Tammy's
a great detective.

03:03.792 --> 03:06.098
Have you heard of the Butcher
of South Worcester?

03:06.142 --> 03:08.623
No.
No one has.

03:08.666 --> 03:12.235
Tammy caught him before he could
even start butchering.

03:12.279 --> 03:14.585
Good Lord.

03:14.629 --> 03:19.242
It's shocking that she's not
higher up on the force.

03:19.286 --> 03:21.984
I bet she's hiding something
weird on her record.

03:22.027 --> 03:23.551
She's good.

03:23.594 --> 03:26.467
She's not gonna rest
until the arsonist --

03:26.510 --> 03:31.254
well, you,I guess --
is behind bars.

03:31.298 --> 03:33.865
Oh!
What are we gonna do?

03:33.909 --> 03:37.869
[ Laughter]

03:37.913 --> 03:40.872
I guess I'm gonna
have to take on Tammy.

03:40.916 --> 03:46.487
Get her over here on my turf
and...work my magic.

03:46.530 --> 03:48.489
Hey. It's late,
what are you doing?

03:48.532 --> 03:50.708
Well, a plan as important
as this can't wait.

03:50.752 --> 03:53.494
I got to jump into action,
get serious.

03:53.537 --> 03:55.104
So you're going
to the bar.

03:55.147 --> 03:56.671
Well, there's a reason
that "drinkin'" rhymes

03:56.714 --> 03:58.368
with "thinkin'."

03:58.412 --> 04:00.892
It's because
I'm good at both.

04:00.936 --> 04:02.633
Don't worry, babe.

04:02.677 --> 04:03.895
Kev-o's on this!

04:03.939 --> 04:05.288
Sleep tight!

04:05.332 --> 04:07.116
[ Laughter]

04:12.730 --> 04:14.123
♪

04:14.166 --> 04:15.472
[Sighs]

04:15.516 --> 04:17.909
♪

04:17.953 --> 04:19.650
[Sighs]

04:19.694 --> 04:22.740
♪

04:22.784 --> 04:23.698
[Huffs]

04:23.741 --> 04:24.699
[Exhales sharply]

04:24.742 --> 04:31.096
♪

04:31.140 --> 04:37.277
♪

04:37.320 --> 04:40.105
[Train horn blows in distance]

04:40.149 --> 04:41.629
Okay.

04:41.672 --> 04:43.326
[Sniffles]
Okay.

04:43.370 --> 04:46.721
[Exhales steadily]

04:46.764 --> 04:50.507
[Footsteps approaching]

04:50.551 --> 04:52.335
Whoa.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.337
You doing yoga
or something?

04:54.381 --> 04:55.773
What?

04:55.817 --> 04:58.950
Oh, no, I'm just trying
clear my head.

04:58.994 --> 05:01.344
Sorry.

05:01.388 --> 05:03.303
Why are you sorry?

05:03.346 --> 05:04.739
No, I'm not --
I'm not sorry.

05:04.782 --> 05:06.001
I just -- I don't know
what I'm saying.

05:06.044 --> 05:07.829
I haven't slept in two days.

05:14.226 --> 05:16.490
[Siren wailing in distance]

05:18.753 --> 05:21.712
Because you're just
so excited to die?

05:23.497 --> 05:26.238
No. 'Cause I feel like
I forgot something.

05:26.282 --> 05:27.457
What'd you forget?

05:27.501 --> 05:30.765
Well, if I knew,
I'd be able to sleep.

05:33.289 --> 05:35.552
Like, I feel like
I dropped something

05:35.596 --> 05:37.206
and I feel it next to me.

05:37.249 --> 05:39.469
And I'm trying to figure out
what it is, and I'm --

05:39.513 --> 05:41.993
I'm lying there wide awake
just convinced

05:42.037 --> 05:44.779
if I don't pick it up, something
terrible's gonna happen.

05:44.822 --> 05:48.391
You know...
what I mean?

05:48.435 --> 05:50.785
That you...

05:50.828 --> 05:52.526
dropped something?

05:52.569 --> 05:54.745
See? I'm not making any sense.
I'm sorry.

05:54.789 --> 05:58.009
No, I'm not sorry.
I'm not -- I'm not sorry.

05:58.053 --> 06:01.491
I -- [Sighs]
Hey.

06:01.535 --> 06:04.015
It's okay.

06:04.059 --> 06:05.582
It's okay.

06:05.626 --> 06:06.583
[Exhales sharply]

06:08.280 --> 06:09.847
So, you can't sleep either?

06:09.891 --> 06:12.633
I haven't slept since I watched
"The NeverEnding Story."

06:12.676 --> 06:14.852
Ugh.

06:14.896 --> 06:17.420
No, this is pretty much
every night for me.

06:17.464 --> 06:19.857
God, that sucks.

06:19.901 --> 06:22.512
I like
this time of night.

06:22.556 --> 06:24.427
It's quiet.

06:24.471 --> 06:26.516
[Mug clattering]

06:26.560 --> 06:29.040
♪

06:29.084 --> 06:31.608
Usually.

06:31.652 --> 06:33.262
But, hey, maybe now
you can get some sleep.

06:33.305 --> 06:35.743
♪

06:35.786 --> 06:37.440
You know
what you dropped.

06:37.484 --> 06:41.096
♪

06:41.139 --> 06:43.272
[Chuckles]
[Chuckles]

06:43.315 --> 06:48.582
♪

06:48.625 --> 06:52.412
I have been on the receiving end
of his bullshit for 15 years.

06:52.455 --> 06:56.459
Why can't I just once
have it work for me?

06:56.503 --> 06:59.331
Well, you can,
but have it work for you

06:59.375 --> 07:03.118
so that Kevin gets you
a new vacuum or something.

07:03.161 --> 07:05.033
A vacuum?
No.

07:05.076 --> 07:07.470
Is that what you think a woman
should get out of her marriages?

07:07.514 --> 07:09.472
No, that's not what I
think a woman should get
out of her marriage.

07:09.516 --> 07:12.432
No, that was stupid.[Sighs]

07:12.475 --> 07:14.564
But I'm not sure you get
moral high ground here.

07:14.608 --> 07:17.480
You know, you are about
to ruin another woman.

07:17.524 --> 07:19.482
I'm not ruining Tammy.
Kevin is.

07:19.526 --> 07:21.136
Yeah, because
you're pushing him to.

07:21.179 --> 07:25.053
No. I'm just nudging
in a direction.

07:25.096 --> 07:26.446
And after that --
who knows?

07:26.489 --> 07:28.317
You know how it'll end.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.797
Okay. Can't we j--

07:29.840 --> 07:33.453
Focus on pulling
your weight here, okay?

07:33.496 --> 07:34.584
Yeah.

07:34.628 --> 07:36.717
I'm losing faith.
[Scoffs]

07:36.760 --> 07:38.719
Is it possible that
this makes my apartment

07:38.762 --> 07:40.285
even more depressing?
No.

07:40.329 --> 07:42.810
Thismakes
your apartment depressing.

07:42.853 --> 07:44.899
This is festive, okay?

07:44.942 --> 07:46.291
I have a vision.

07:48.729 --> 07:50.600
Allison...

07:50.644 --> 07:53.342
if Kevin's decided
Tammy's a problem,

07:53.385 --> 07:56.127
she won't be a cop
in three days.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.521
Okay, well, maybe
she shouldn't be a cop.

07:58.565 --> 07:59.870
She planted evidence
for her partner.

07:59.914 --> 08:02.525
Maybe she's asking
for what's coming to her.

08:02.569 --> 08:04.658
But she's
Patty's girlfriend.

08:04.701 --> 08:07.138
[Sighs] Well,
maybe Patty deserves better.

08:07.182 --> 08:10.751
Allison --
Sam!

08:10.794 --> 08:12.317
This is how I stay.

08:12.361 --> 08:16.365
[Music playing indistinctly
in distance]

08:16.408 --> 08:19.542
Okay.

08:19.586 --> 08:21.892
I just want to make sure
you're still you

08:21.936 --> 08:23.328
on the other side of it.

08:25.896 --> 08:27.245
I know what I'm doing.

08:30.161 --> 08:31.728
Hmm.
Mm.

08:31.772 --> 08:34.209
Diane: Okay, I know
I still got something.

08:34.252 --> 08:35.689
Thanks, D.
Yeah.

08:35.732 --> 08:39.301
Sleeping pills,
anti "anxiety" pills --

08:39.344 --> 08:42.391
and...
good old pain killers.

08:42.434 --> 08:43.871
But those will knock you
right out.

08:43.914 --> 08:46.569
Yeah, well, I'll take anything
at this point, so...

08:46.613 --> 08:48.919
Thank you.
Take 'em.

08:48.963 --> 08:51.443
Insomnia is no joke.
[Chuckles]

08:51.487 --> 08:53.184
Dr. Gaetz put me
on just about everything

08:53.228 --> 08:55.752
when I wasn't sleeping
those couple of months.

08:55.796 --> 08:58.407
And did -- uh,
did any of them work?

08:58.450 --> 09:01.802
Well, what worked was me
making Chuck

09:01.845 --> 09:04.239
buy a mattress
that wasn't 45 years old.

09:04.282 --> 09:06.546
[Chuckles]

09:07.808 --> 09:11.376
You up all night
thinking about something?

09:11.420 --> 09:15.946
Uh, vacation,
stuff like that?

09:15.990 --> 09:17.992
Yeah.

09:18.035 --> 09:19.776
Stuff like that.

09:19.820 --> 09:23.127
[Music playing indistinctly
on radio in distance]

09:23.171 --> 09:24.389
Okay.

09:24.433 --> 09:28.480
Well, I'm --
I'm here, you know.

09:28.524 --> 09:30.831
As long as you need.

09:30.874 --> 09:32.572
Thanks, D.

09:34.748 --> 09:36.576
I don't deserve it.

09:36.619 --> 09:39.143
Hey.

09:39.187 --> 09:42.407
Sure you do.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.801
You warned me
about Neil, huh?

09:44.845 --> 09:48.588
Should've listened to you
the first time.

09:48.631 --> 09:53.157
Eh, I spent
Chuck's block party savings

09:53.201 --> 09:55.986
bailing him
out a couple of nights ago.

09:56.030 --> 09:58.510
You bailed him out?
I, uh -- [Chuckles nervously]

09:58.554 --> 10:00.948
I thought he was supposed to be
stuck in there for the weekend.

10:00.991 --> 10:02.993
[Scoffs]
He probably should be.

10:03.037 --> 10:07.389
I -- I took him home,
and he kept drinking.

10:07.432 --> 10:10.000
Barely even looked at me.

10:10.044 --> 10:11.741
Eventually
he just got fed up

10:11.785 --> 10:15.658
and then he stormed out
of his own place.

10:15.702 --> 10:18.226
I -- I haven't heard
from him since.

10:18.269 --> 10:20.794
Mm.
Yeah.

10:20.837 --> 10:27.235
Allison, I'm -- I'm trying
really hard not to care...

10:27.278 --> 10:29.629
but -- but I kind of think
he's losing it.

10:32.327 --> 10:33.676
What do you mean?

10:33.720 --> 10:37.506
He kept talking about
this crazy story he had.

10:37.549 --> 10:40.509
I mean, it was -- it was --
it was really awful.

10:40.552 --> 10:42.467
I wouldn't even
wanna repeat it.

10:45.862 --> 10:49.083
I know that all marriages
have problems.

10:49.126 --> 10:50.301
Mm-hmm.

10:50.345 --> 10:52.216
But what Neil said
you did to Kevin?

10:52.260 --> 10:54.523
[Chuckles]

10:54.566 --> 10:55.872
I -- I'm --
I'm starting to think

10:55.916 --> 10:57.569
that he should be
in a padded room in Danvers

10:57.613 --> 10:59.310
and not in a jail cell.

10:59.354 --> 11:01.704
[Sighs]

11:01.748 --> 11:04.185
♪

11:07.841 --> 11:09.407
Patty: Hang on!

11:10.931 --> 11:12.715
Neil.

11:12.759 --> 11:14.586
What?
Neil.
The thing I dropped.

11:14.630 --> 11:16.240
The thing that's
about to blow up -- it's Neil.

11:16.284 --> 11:18.242
Shocker,
but my brilliant plan of

11:18.286 --> 11:21.071
"hope he approaches this
rationally" isn't working.What do you mean?

11:21.115 --> 11:22.943
Isn't he sweating out red wine
in the drunk tank?

11:22.986 --> 11:24.509
Nope.
Wait --

11:24.553 --> 11:26.511
Nope, nope, nope.
What?

11:26.555 --> 11:28.862
He was bailed out days ago --
he hasn't been home yet?

11:28.905 --> 11:31.299
No.
Did Kevin bail him out?

11:31.342 --> 11:32.343
No, Diane did.

11:32.387 --> 11:34.389
Diane.

11:34.432 --> 11:35.695
Diane, like your aunt?

11:35.738 --> 11:37.348
Yeah -- they're --
they're --

11:37.392 --> 11:38.393
they're seeing each other.

11:38.436 --> 11:39.916
Seeing each other.

11:39.960 --> 11:41.875
Like because he's at the
package store all the time?

11:41.918 --> 11:45.269
Mm. No. Because they meet up
at Worcester View Suites

11:45.313 --> 11:47.054
to have sex.

11:47.097 --> 11:49.273
What?
Since when?

11:49.317 --> 11:50.710
Well, I --
like a month or so.

11:50.753 --> 11:52.407
And you knew this
but didn't tell me?

11:52.450 --> 11:54.104
I thought it was over,
okay?

11:54.148 --> 11:55.715
Anyway,
Diane bailed him out.

11:55.758 --> 11:57.064
She doesn't know
where he is.

11:57.107 --> 11:58.587
He's probably wandering
around the streets

11:58.630 --> 11:59.719
of Worcester,
drunk --

11:59.762 --> 12:01.155
Is he okay?

12:01.198 --> 12:04.375
Oh. Hey, Tammy. Sorry,
I didn't know you were here.

12:04.419 --> 12:05.594
Oh, nothing
to be sorry about.

12:05.637 --> 12:06.943
Do you want me
to help find him?

12:06.987 --> 12:08.771
No.

12:08.815 --> 12:11.165
No.
Well, what you said before --

12:11.208 --> 12:14.298
you know, he needs to learn
how to take care of himself.

12:14.342 --> 12:15.996
Yeah, yes.

12:16.039 --> 12:18.607
He's got to figure this one
out on his own.

12:18.650 --> 12:20.130
I-I can't do this anymore.

12:20.174 --> 12:21.828
Are you sure?

12:24.134 --> 12:26.658
He's an adult.

12:26.702 --> 12:30.314
Okay.
Well, uh, stay strong.

12:30.358 --> 12:32.882
I'm gonna get out of here
and leave you two alone.

12:32.926 --> 12:34.797
I'm heading out, actually.
I'll walk out with you.

12:34.841 --> 12:36.756
Okay. Bye.Bye.

12:39.454 --> 12:41.151
Milady.

12:50.204 --> 12:52.032
Hey.

12:52.075 --> 12:54.774
You think Neil's actually
gonna be alright?

12:54.817 --> 12:59.996
Uh, I think he's capable of more
than people give him credit for.

13:00.040 --> 13:01.476
Uh, your husband asked me

13:01.519 --> 13:02.912
to come by your place
when he gets off work.

13:02.956 --> 13:05.828
You have any idea
what that's about?

13:05.872 --> 13:09.397
Kevin?
I never really know with him.

13:09.440 --> 13:10.964
Sorry.

13:11.007 --> 13:13.836
[Dogs barking in distance]

13:13.880 --> 13:15.925
♪

13:15.969 --> 13:18.275
Hey, it's Ridgeway.

13:18.319 --> 13:19.929
Can you give me a heads-up
if anyone comes in

13:19.973 --> 13:21.670
by the name of Neil O'Connor?

13:21.713 --> 13:23.585
[ Ringing,
answering machine beeps]

13:23.628 --> 13:24.847
Patty: What?Patty.

13:24.891 --> 13:27.589
Uh, I have to
go find Neil.

13:27.632 --> 13:30.244
Just call me back,
and I'll explain, okay?

13:30.287 --> 13:31.854
I just saw you. Why -- Why
didn't you pick up the phone?

13:31.898 --> 13:32.812
You okay?

13:32.855 --> 13:35.249
[Ceiling fan whirring]

13:35.292 --> 13:41.472
♪

13:41.516 --> 13:42.647
Neil?

13:42.691 --> 13:46.913
♪

13:52.309 --> 13:56.052
♪

13:56.096 --> 13:58.402
Hey, Dad!
Congratulations!

13:58.446 --> 14:01.057
I see that growth
on your arm disappeared!

14:01.101 --> 14:03.277
What? I didn't have
a growth on my arm.

14:03.320 --> 14:05.496
Sure you did,
her name was Lorraine.

14:05.540 --> 14:06.846
[ Laughter]

14:06.889 --> 14:08.978
[Cheerfully]
Did you guys break up?

14:09.022 --> 14:10.197
I mean...

14:10.240 --> 14:13.417
[somber]
did you guys break up?

14:13.461 --> 14:15.419
No, we did not break up.

14:15.463 --> 14:17.682
She just doesn't love
coming around here.

14:17.726 --> 14:18.988
Oh. Great.
[Chuckles]

14:19.032 --> 14:20.642
[Knocking]

14:20.685 --> 14:22.862
Ah, that must be Tammy.

14:22.905 --> 14:24.298
Alright,
you want an arsonist?

14:24.341 --> 14:26.909
I'll give you an arsonist.

14:26.953 --> 14:28.302
Scram, old man!

14:28.345 --> 14:31.871
[ Laughter]

14:31.914 --> 14:34.525
"Entree-voo sivoo plate."

14:34.569 --> 14:38.051
[ Laughter]

14:38.094 --> 14:41.141
Welcome to my
Sherlock "home,"

14:41.184 --> 14:42.882
Detective.

14:42.925 --> 14:44.361
Can I offer you a water?

14:44.405 --> 14:46.102
Sure, thanks.

14:46.146 --> 14:48.322
Here's the thing --
I didn't expect you to say yes,

14:48.365 --> 14:51.368
so I don't have
any water available.

14:51.412 --> 14:53.501
Touché.

14:53.544 --> 14:56.069
I have things to do.
What do you need, Kevin?

14:56.112 --> 14:58.114
Here's the thing --
I've been thinking about

14:58.158 --> 15:00.943
