17:13.119 --> 17:14.859
Can I help you?

17:14.903 --> 17:16.426
♪ And I sit alone

17:16.470 --> 17:18.037
Hello?
Hi.

17:18.080 --> 17:19.429
You lose
your room key again?

17:19.473 --> 17:21.214
Uh, no.
I don't have a room here.

17:21.257 --> 17:24.043
Are you sure?

17:24.086 --> 17:25.957
Yeah. Yes.

17:26.001 --> 17:28.177
Huh. Okay.

17:28.221 --> 17:30.484
Uh, it's $20 an hour,
$80 for the night.

17:30.527 --> 17:33.052
Uh, no, uh,
I don't want a room.

17:33.095 --> 17:35.967
I'm -- I'm looking
for a friend.

17:36.011 --> 17:38.883
Uh, Neil O'Connor?

17:38.927 --> 17:42.061
He has shorter hair now.
He comes with Diane McAntee.

17:42.104 --> 17:44.933
Kind of an odd couple.

17:44.976 --> 17:46.239
I thought
they were kinda cute.

17:46.282 --> 17:47.936
Okay, so
you -- you know them.

17:47.979 --> 17:49.416
Uh, is he here?

17:49.459 --> 17:52.288
♪

17:52.332 --> 17:55.422
Hmm. Okay.

17:55.465 --> 17:57.554
Okay, what?

17:57.598 --> 17:59.121
Nothing.

17:59.165 --> 18:02.124
Wh-- What just --
What just happened to you?

18:02.168 --> 18:07.651
Look, telling you if he's here
is against motel code.

18:07.695 --> 18:09.436
"Motel code"?

18:09.479 --> 18:10.785
Of conduct.

18:10.828 --> 18:12.961
As a general rule,

18:13.004 --> 18:15.485
I don't rat
out anyone's husbands.

18:15.529 --> 18:17.270
Or wives.Oh, no, no, no, no.

18:17.313 --> 18:19.141
He's not my husband.
Or boyfriend.

18:19.185 --> 18:23.798
God, um, no.
I am -- I'm worried about him.

18:23.841 --> 18:26.975
Really w-- Really worried.
So, can you, um --

18:27.018 --> 18:29.369
can you please
just tell me if he's here?

18:29.412 --> 18:32.328
[Sighs]

18:32.372 --> 18:38.378
I guess I'd have to worry, too,
if your "buddy" was here.

18:38.421 --> 18:40.902
But, no, he's not.

18:40.945 --> 18:44.732
I think they were in here
last week, but that's it.

18:44.775 --> 18:47.604
♪

18:47.648 --> 18:48.562
Thank you.

18:48.605 --> 18:54.350
♪

18:54.394 --> 19:00.226
♪

19:02.445 --> 19:04.621
I'm assuming
Neil's not here?

19:04.665 --> 19:06.797
Uh, no.

19:06.841 --> 19:08.190
You're --
Yup.

19:08.234 --> 19:10.279
Same as you.
Of course.

19:10.323 --> 19:12.194
That's, uh --
That's really nice of you.

19:12.238 --> 19:14.370
You don't have to do that,
though. 'Cause I'm happy to.

19:14.414 --> 19:17.591
I -- I checked the Seas.
Rosetti's.

19:17.634 --> 19:19.375
And I checked the hospital,
the drunk tank,

19:19.419 --> 19:21.029
and the gazebo
behind the library

19:21.072 --> 19:23.162
where he likes to
smoke weed.

19:23.205 --> 19:24.380
Well, I guess
neither of us listen

19:24.424 --> 19:26.600
when Patty said
she didn't want help.

19:26.643 --> 19:30.821
Hm. Well, Patty doesn't always
know what's best for her.

19:33.824 --> 19:35.609
Come on. You're not gonna say
that that's not fair to her

19:35.652 --> 19:37.828
or I really don't know her?

19:40.831 --> 19:42.790
Nope.

19:42.833 --> 19:45.227
Allison,
I told you to back off.

19:45.271 --> 19:48.230
You instigate, and you got
her into this shit.

19:48.274 --> 19:51.320
And you're only thinking
about yourself.

19:51.364 --> 19:54.628
Now, you might not be
on that video...

19:54.671 --> 19:57.196
but I feel like you were
right there next to her.

19:59.285 --> 20:01.156
What, you're not gonna
say anything?

20:05.247 --> 20:06.901
I just don't think I can
say anything

20:06.944 --> 20:08.424
right to you
at this point.

20:08.468 --> 20:10.861
♪

20:10.905 --> 20:13.037
[Sighs]

20:13.081 --> 20:18.217
♪

20:18.260 --> 20:23.134
♪

20:23.178 --> 20:27.269
[Siren wailing in distance]

20:27.313 --> 20:33.275
♪

20:33.319 --> 20:34.668
[Cellphone lock screen clicks]

20:34.711 --> 20:37.105
♪

20:37.148 --> 20:41.892
[ Ringing,
answering machine beeps]

20:41.936 --> 20:43.416
Patty: What?

20:43.459 --> 20:47.463
♪

20:47.507 --> 20:49.465
[Brakes squeal]

20:49.509 --> 20:52.251
♪

20:57.168 --> 20:58.779
[Engine shuts off]

21:03.218 --> 21:05.699
Whoa.
You cleaned.

21:05.742 --> 21:08.615
Yeah.
I had to do something.

21:08.658 --> 21:10.660
I saw the light.
I thought it was him.

21:10.704 --> 21:13.707
Is he still not --
No.

21:13.750 --> 21:15.404
Patty,
we have to find him.

21:15.448 --> 21:18.146
He's like a live grenade
running around town.

21:18.189 --> 21:20.975
He told Diane everything.

21:21.018 --> 21:24.457
He was wasted, so she didn't
believe him, but we got lucky.

21:24.500 --> 21:26.285
Tammy's looking for him.

21:26.328 --> 21:27.764
She is?
I told her not to.

21:27.808 --> 21:32.291
Well, it's Tammy,
alright?

21:32.334 --> 21:33.944
Jesus,
when will this ever stop?

21:35.990 --> 21:39.341
[Sighs]

21:39.385 --> 21:41.430
Wait a minute.

21:41.474 --> 21:42.910
What does
any of this matter?

21:42.953 --> 21:45.739
Well, Tammy's a cop,
and we're...criminals.

21:45.782 --> 21:47.349
If you want to look at it
in black and white.

21:47.393 --> 21:49.699
No, what does this matter
if you're gone?

21:49.743 --> 21:51.179
Neil can say
whatever he wants.

21:51.222 --> 21:52.441
That's the point,
right?

21:52.485 --> 21:54.008
And I can blame you
for everything.

21:54.051 --> 21:56.097
You just have to go...

21:56.140 --> 21:58.795
soon.

21:58.839 --> 22:01.363
Um, I didn't want to say
anything until I thought

22:01.407 --> 22:02.973
it was possible,

22:03.017 --> 22:06.194
but I, um...

22:06.237 --> 22:09.240
I want to stay.

22:09.284 --> 22:11.330
You -- You do? Why?

22:11.373 --> 22:13.767
And I-I think I can, but I know
you're only helping me

22:13.810 --> 22:15.029
so you can
get me out of here.

22:15.072 --> 22:17.336
And I pulled you into this,
so if you --

22:17.379 --> 22:18.554
if you still
want me to go --

22:18.598 --> 22:19.729
No.

22:23.298 --> 22:24.386
I don't.

22:24.430 --> 22:30.523
♪

22:30.566 --> 22:32.829
What do we have to do?

22:32.873 --> 22:34.396
Um, okay.

22:34.440 --> 22:37.704
So, call Tammy, tell her
to stop looking for him

22:37.747 --> 22:39.358
'cause I need to
him first.

22:39.401 --> 22:40.620
Okay.
I can come with you.

22:40.663 --> 22:43.579
No. Just stay here in case
he comes back.

22:43.623 --> 22:46.365
Okay. But if you find him,
bring him back here.

22:46.408 --> 22:47.844
We'll talk to him together.Okay.

22:47.888 --> 22:50.412
And I will try to figure out,
um, other places

22:50.456 --> 22:52.022
he might be, okay?

22:52.066 --> 22:53.023
Maybe Kevin knows.

22:53.067 --> 22:54.634
Alright.
Whoa.

22:54.677 --> 22:57.419
Hey.

22:57.463 --> 23:00.727
Allison...go home.

23:00.770 --> 23:02.250
Get some rest.

23:02.293 --> 23:06.036
You're not gonna find him
tonight.

23:06.080 --> 23:09.431
We'll figure it out.

23:09.475 --> 23:11.868
Promise?

23:11.912 --> 23:13.522
Promise.

23:13.566 --> 23:19.398
♪

23:19.441 --> 23:20.573
Good night.

23:20.616 --> 23:22.096
Good night.

23:22.139 --> 23:23.402
[Door opens, closes]

23:27.362 --> 23:28.842
[Birds chirping]

23:28.885 --> 23:36.458
♪

23:36.502 --> 23:38.460
[Sighs]

23:38.504 --> 23:47.991
♪

23:48.035 --> 23:57.479
♪

23:57.523 --> 23:59.220
[Sighs]

23:59.263 --> 24:04.051
♪

24:04.094 --> 24:07.533
[ Laughter]

24:09.970 --> 24:11.450
Hey, babe.

24:11.493 --> 24:16.019
Which is better --
classic, or...

24:16.063 --> 24:17.064
flip-ups?

24:17.107 --> 24:18.152
Uh...

24:18.195 --> 24:20.241
uh, both.
Ah!

24:20.284 --> 24:21.851
I like the way
you're thinking lately.

24:21.895 --> 24:23.287
Wicked smart.

24:23.331 --> 24:25.028
Smart?
I'm out of it.

24:25.072 --> 24:26.595
This morning I tried
to brush my teeth

24:26.639 --> 24:28.118
with your
nose hair trimmer.

24:28.162 --> 24:30.512
That is so gross!

24:30.556 --> 24:34.734
I have to put that thing
up my nose!

24:34.777 --> 24:37.519
You know, I think I'm gonna go
with the classic.

24:37.563 --> 24:39.390
I've got to go down
to the Police Department today

24:39.434 --> 24:41.305
and I wanna look appropriate.

24:41.349 --> 24:43.090
The Police Department?

24:43.133 --> 24:44.483
Oh, no, does --
does Tammy know

24:44.526 --> 24:45.919
that you're the one
who set the fire?

24:45.962 --> 24:47.486
Not yet.

24:47.529 --> 24:50.314
I tried to throw her off
my scent, but she's very good.

24:50.358 --> 24:53.361
To be fair, you have
a very pungent smell.

24:53.404 --> 24:56.407
Strange notes of vanilla.

24:56.451 --> 24:57.887
That's just cake.

24:57.931 --> 24:59.715
But I made
some phone calls,

24:59.759 --> 25:03.327
and turns out, shockingly,
that you were right.

25:03.371 --> 25:05.852
Tammy is totally shady.

25:05.895 --> 25:09.377
Apparently, she planted evidence
to help that partner of hers,

25:09.420 --> 25:12.162
you know, the one
who died on the toilet.

25:12.206 --> 25:16.558
By the way, I think that's
an incredibly manly way to go.

25:16.602 --> 25:20.388
He was peeing sitting down.I take back
everything I said.

25:20.431 --> 25:23.391
Anyway, I'm got to go to
the ol' police station to see

25:23.434 --> 25:25.436
if I can use this info
against Tammy

25:25.480 --> 25:27.308
before she tosses me
in jail.

25:27.351 --> 25:29.571
Now, before you go trying
to talk me out of it --

25:29.615 --> 25:31.530
That's smart.

25:31.573 --> 25:34.097
Wow.

25:34.141 --> 25:37.448
I want to encourage
more of this behavior.

25:37.492 --> 25:40.582
Remind me to tell Neil
to do something nice for you.

25:40.626 --> 25:42.236
From me.

25:42.279 --> 25:43.977
That's...

25:44.020 --> 25:45.544
almost thoughtful.

25:45.587 --> 25:47.894
Speaking of Neil, uh,
have you seen him lately?

25:47.937 --> 25:50.418
Uh, not since
I Usain Bolt'ed from the cops

25:50.461 --> 25:54.944
and he abandoned me by running
too slow and getting arrested.

25:54.988 --> 25:56.598
That is his own fault.

25:56.642 --> 25:57.599
But he's been out
for a few days,

25:57.643 --> 25:58.992
and Patty's
getting worried.

25:59.035 --> 26:00.820
Well, he's probably
at Maloney's.

26:00.863 --> 26:02.691
Did you guys boycott that place
when they said

26:02.735 --> 26:05.825
you couldn't lean over the bar
and drink directly from the tap?

26:05.868 --> 26:08.131
So rude!

26:08.175 --> 26:12.614
My lips barely
touched the spigot.Touched the spigot, I know.

26:12.658 --> 26:15.965
But that place does have Keno,
and you know how Neil loves

26:16.009 --> 26:18.925
to get lost in the numbers
when he gets out of jail.

26:18.968 --> 26:20.709
You should probably
go check there.

26:20.753 --> 26:23.364
That is actually,
uh, very helpful.

26:23.407 --> 26:25.279
So, thank you.
Ah.

26:25.322 --> 26:27.020
Hey, Allison?

26:27.063 --> 26:28.499
You're welcome.

26:28.543 --> 26:30.806
Awww!
God, right in the eye.

26:30.850 --> 26:32.939
Damn it, right in the eye.

26:32.982 --> 26:38.945
♪ Since you came along,
everything's alright ♪

26:38.988 --> 26:41.034
Neil.

26:41.077 --> 26:42.165
Neil.

26:42.209 --> 26:43.384
What the hell
are you doing?

26:43.427 --> 26:44.994
[Sniffles]

26:45.038 --> 26:46.256
Playing Keno.

26:46.300 --> 26:47.867
You know what I mean.

26:47.910 --> 26:49.520
Diane bailed you out.
You disappeared for days.

26:49.564 --> 26:51.174
No one knew
where you were.

26:51.218 --> 26:53.263
Oh, sure, like suddenly
you're concerned about me.

26:53.307 --> 26:56.049
I'm concerned that you told
Diane what happened.

26:56.092 --> 26:57.616
You cannot do that.

27:01.707 --> 27:02.838
Okay.

27:02.882 --> 27:05.885
Okay, how about
I take you home?

27:05.928 --> 27:08.278
We get out of here,
and we can talk about it?

27:08.322 --> 27:11.673
[Clears throat]
I don't want to talk to you.

27:11.717 --> 27:14.284
[Sniffles]

27:14.328 --> 27:15.764
But I need a ride.

27:15.808 --> 27:16.896
A ride home?

27:16.939 --> 27:19.899
No, somewhere else.

27:19.942 --> 27:22.075
It's urgent.

27:22.118 --> 27:23.467
And you're going
to take me there.

27:23.511 --> 27:26.209
I -- I mean,I could always hitch-hike.

27:26.253 --> 27:27.776
Take a crowded bus.

27:27.820 --> 27:29.343
See if anyone wants to hear
a really good story!

27:29.386 --> 27:30.910
No -- I'll take you.

27:30.953 --> 27:34.261
I will take you, okay?

27:34.304 --> 27:35.305
Okay.

27:35.349 --> 27:38.526
♪

27:38.569 --> 27:39.875
[Exhales sharply]
Okay.

27:39.919 --> 27:40.876
Oh.

27:43.705 --> 27:45.489
You'll pay for these.

27:45.533 --> 27:55.674
♪

27:55.717 --> 27:57.284
Thank you.

28:05.727 --> 28:09.600
I know this whole thing
has taken a toll on you.

28:09.644 --> 28:12.081
And it's taken a toll
on me, too.

28:12.125 --> 28:16.042
You know, no one wanted
this to happen.

28:16.085 --> 28:18.827
Stay left at the fork.

28:18.871 --> 28:21.961
Yeah.

28:22.004 --> 28:23.702
I know I haven't said this,
but I --

28:23.745 --> 28:26.617
I am sorry.

28:26.661 --> 28:28.271
For a lot of things.

28:28.315 --> 28:32.928
And I feel like on some level,
maybe you are, too.

28:32.972 --> 28:34.930
Maybe we've
both made mistakes,

28:34.974 --> 28:38.891
and maybe
we can get past them.

28:41.197 --> 28:42.721
I can if you can.

28:50.772 --> 28:52.731
You look like shit.

28:57.823 --> 28:59.476
I feel like shit.

29:04.046 --> 29:05.961
Yeah.
Join the club.

29:06.005 --> 29:08.094
Right here, right here,
pull into this lot.

29:08.137 --> 29:13.577
♪

29:13.621 --> 29:19.105
♪

29:19.148 --> 29:20.541
Your urgent thing
is skating?

29:20.584 --> 29:21.803
Wait here.

29:21.847 --> 29:22.978
No, I'm not gonna
wait here, Neil --

29:23.022 --> 29:24.240
I'm not gonna
say anything!

29:24.284 --> 29:26.199
Just...wait here.

29:26.242 --> 29:30.638
♪

29:30.681 --> 29:32.988
[Sighs]

29:33.032 --> 29:39.778
♪

29:39.821 --> 29:43.738
[Cellphone vibrating]

29:48.525 --> 29:51.354
Allison?Hey. Hey.

29:51.398 --> 29:53.443
I found him.

29:53.487 --> 29:55.010
You did?
Is he okay?

29:55.054 --> 29:58.274
No. No. He's a mess,
but he's gonna be fine.

29:58.318 --> 29:59.667
Oh, God.

29:59.710 --> 30:01.234
So, you talk
to Diane and Tammy,

30:01.277 --> 30:02.931
but we have to keep
people away until --

30:02.975 --> 30:04.454
until we can
figure this out.

30:04.498 --> 30:07.240
Okay.
Uh, are you coming back here?

30:07.283 --> 30:08.632
Uh, soon.

30:08.676 --> 30:10.939
We had to make a detour.

30:10.983 --> 30:13.202
But we'll be back.
So, talk to Diane.

30:13.246 --> 30:14.377
Talk to Tammy.

30:14.421 --> 30:15.988
And I got him.

30:16.031 --> 30:17.946
Okay.
I'll see you soon.

30:17.990 --> 30:19.165
Bye.

30:19.208 --> 30:21.036
♪

30:21.080 --> 30:22.821
[Exhales sharply]

30:22.864 --> 30:27.651
♪

30:27.695 --> 30:29.740
[ Ringing]

30:29.784 --> 30:30.959
Tammy: This is Tammy.
Leave a message.

30:31.003 --> 30:32.656
[ Answering machine beeps]

30:32.700 --> 30:36.878
Hey, uh,
I've been calling you.

30:36.922 --> 30:39.881
A lot.
Um, I found Neil, he's fine.

30:39.925 --> 30:41.317
So you just, um --

30:41.361 --> 30:45.191
If you could please
just call me back.

30:45.234 --> 30:50.457
♪

30:50.500 --> 30:52.067
Goddamn it!

30:54.548 --> 30:56.680
What happened?

30:56.724 --> 30:58.117
Those dicks banned me
a couple weeks ago

30:58.160 --> 31:00.293
and they still won't
let me back in.

31:00.336 --> 31:02.730
What? You got banned
from an ice rink?

31:02.773 --> 31:04.732
I thought this was
the one of places you were,

31:04.775 --> 31:06.429
like, well regarded.

31:06.473 --> 31:08.997
It was a stupid accident,
it wasn't my fault.

31:09.041 --> 31:10.520
And they still won't --
Ugh!

31:10.564 --> 31:12.871
[Sniffles, huffs]

31:15.134 --> 31:17.658
♪

31:17.701 --> 31:19.312
This means a lot to you?

31:23.142 --> 31:24.056
Okay.

31:25.579 --> 31:27.276
Come on.

31:30.801 --> 31:31.890
Come on.

31:36.590 --> 31:38.897
[Door bell dings]

31:40.420 --> 31:42.335
Hey.

31:42.378 --> 31:44.032
Patty.

31:44.076 --> 31:46.121
You know Allison doesn't
work here anymore, right?

31:46.165 --> 31:48.558
Yeah.
I know.

31:48.602 --> 31:51.953
Uh...

31:51.997 --> 31:55.609
I came to talk to you,
actually.

31:55.652 --> 31:57.785
We found Neil,
he's okay.

31:57.828 --> 31:59.830
Oh, yeah?

31:59.874 --> 32:01.745
Yeah.
He's on his way home.

32:01.789 --> 32:02.964
And I just wanted to say
thank you

32:03.008 --> 32:04.835
for bailing him
out the other night.

32:04.879 --> 32:07.534
But you should know, if you're
gonna, like, be around him,

32:07.577 --> 32:08.970
this is what he does,
you know?

32:09.014 --> 32:10.754
He goes on a bender
for a couple of days

32:10.798 --> 32:13.801
and then comes back just in time
to eat whatever delicious meal

32:13.844 --> 32:15.107
you just made
for yourself.

32:15.150 --> 32:19.328
I'm not gonna be around,
so don't worry.

32:19.372 --> 32:20.590
I'll leave him alone.

32:20.634 --> 32:22.941
No, D...

32:22.984 --> 32:24.420
that's not what I meant.
I just -- If y--

32:24.464 --> 32:28.163
If you're gonna hang out
with Neil, you got to...

32:28.207 --> 32:30.644
Well, I worry about you,
not him.

32:30.687 --> 32:31.819
I'm a big girl, Patty.

32:31.862 --> 32:33.777
I can take care of myself.

32:33.821 --> 32:37.085
Okay, well, you started
this thing with him,

32:37.129 --> 32:39.131
so I guess
we could both say

32:39.174 --> 32:40.959
that your judgment's
just a little bit off.

32:46.007 --> 32:47.182
I'm sorry.

32:47.226 --> 32:54.363
♪

32:54.407 --> 32:56.409
When I met Chuck,
it was...

32:58.063 --> 33:02.806
It was like a choice,
you know?

33:02.850 --> 33:04.765
I decided to love him.

33:04.808 --> 33:06.593
But with Neil, it's...

33:06.636 --> 33:09.552
Wait.
You love Neil?

33:09.596 --> 33:10.727
I don't know.

33:13.904 --> 33:16.646
Maybe I just don't want
to be alone.

33:16.690 --> 33:19.127
And maybe there's
not always a difference.

33:19.171 --> 33:28.354
♪

33:28.397 --> 33:33.359
[Upbeat music playing
indistinctly]

33:33.402 --> 33:40.061
♪

33:40.105 --> 33:43.021
Uh, you're good.

33:43.064 --> 33:44.022
What?

33:44.065 --> 33:46.024
How?

33:46.067 --> 33:49.897
Kevin. He knows the guy
who drives the Zamboni.

33:49.940 --> 33:52.073
Big Mike Galante.

33:52.117 --> 33:55.076
Kev kept promising
to introduce me, but never did.

33:55.120 --> 33:57.296
Yeah, well, I guess he pulls
some weight around here,

33:57.339 --> 34:01.474
and "Mrs. McRoberts"
pulls some weight, too.

34:01.517 --> 34:06.218
Uh, so I said you made a mistake
and that you were sorry.

34:06.261 --> 34:08.089
And, um, there's a pair
of skates

34:08.133 --> 34:10.004
at the front desk for you,
so...

34:10.744 --> 34:12.354
...have fun.

34:12.398 --> 34:20.449
♪

34:23.800 --> 34:25.976
Hey! Where you going?

34:26.020 --> 34:28.109
My buddy Doug's.
He lives around here.

34:28.153 --> 34:29.719
Well, I just spent
the last hour

34:29.763 --> 34:32.505
pleading with a guy named
Big Mike, and you're leaving?

34:32.548 --> 34:34.855
I don't care
about skating anymore.

34:34.898 --> 34:36.204
So you're
just wasting my time?

34:36.248 --> 34:39.686
No, it's for Patty.

34:39.729 --> 34:41.514
I got us both banned,
and she likes coming here

34:41.557 --> 34:43.298
on her birthday.

34:43.342 --> 34:45.344
You're doing something
for Patty?

34:45.387 --> 34:48.999
Someone should, right?

34:49.043 --> 34:51.089
She's been
through enough.

34:51.132 --> 34:53.874
Yeah, all the stuff
you put her through.

34:53.917 --> 34:55.571
Me?

34:55.615 --> 34:58.661
Since you started coming around,
I barely recognize her.

34:58.705 --> 34:59.967
She's all...

35:00.010 --> 35:01.142
different.

35:01.186 --> 35:02.143
Worse.

35:02.187 --> 35:04.276
No. She's not.

35:04.319 --> 35:05.538
She never bottled me
in the back of the head

35:05.581 --> 35:07.148
before
being friends with you.

35:07.192 --> 35:08.758
Never almost
murdered someone.

35:08.802 --> 35:10.760
Shut up, Neil!

35:10.804 --> 35:15.330
You know I can make your life
a lot more difficult, right?

35:15.374 --> 35:17.985
You don't need to.I don't need to?

35:18.028 --> 35:20.553
You told Diane.
Yeah.

35:20.596 --> 35:23.947
And I told my buddy Doug,
and two kids I met on the bus.

35:23.991 --> 35:25.819
Jesus, I told Kevin
when I found out.

35:25.862 --> 35:29.344
What?
He laughed.

35:29.388 --> 35:31.390
He didn't listen to me
at all.

35:31.433 --> 35:33.043
No one listens to me.

35:33.087 --> 35:35.176
No one.

35:35.220 --> 35:39.137
You can make my life
more difficult?

35:39.180 --> 35:42.052
I'm not a problem
for you.

35:42.096 --> 35:44.272
I've never been a problem
for you.

35:44.316 --> 35:46.492
♪

35:46.535 --> 35:48.581
So, please...

35:48.624 --> 35:52.150
just stay
the hell away from me.

35:53.716 --> 35:55.153
And Patty.

35:56.632 --> 35:57.807
Okay?

35:57.851 --> 36:03.813
♪

36:03.857 --> 36:09.819
♪

36:13.258 --> 36:15.390
Hey, you.

36:15.434 --> 36:17.087
I've been calling you.

36:17.131 --> 36:18.393
How long you been here?

36:18.437 --> 36:20.003
I let myself in.

36:20.047 --> 36:21.788
I figured it was okay.

36:21.831 --> 36:23.398
We're about to
live together.

36:23.442 --> 36:24.747
Of course.
It's fine.

36:24.791 --> 36:26.967
I just -- I didn't know
you were here.

36:27.010 --> 36:30.057
Except I don't --
I don't think we can.

36:30.100 --> 36:32.668
Live together.

36:32.712 --> 36:34.017
What --

36:36.716 --> 36:38.152
We can't?

36:39.675 --> 36:41.851
I really wanted
to ignore this.

36:41.895 --> 36:44.419
I've done my best
to ignore a lot.

36:44.463 --> 36:46.595
Um, and I thought if we moved
in together

36:46.639 --> 36:51.078
and kept moving forward,
but that wasn't the problem.

36:51.121 --> 36:52.645
Allison's
not the problem.

36:57.171 --> 36:59.042
This is.

36:59.086 --> 37:01.001
And I'm sorry.
I can't let it go.

37:01.044 --> 37:02.394
Tammy, let what go?

37:02.437 --> 37:03.873
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

37:03.917 --> 37:05.440
You can take it.

37:05.484 --> 37:07.094
I've seen enough already.

37:07.137 --> 37:15.233
♪

37:15.276 --> 37:17.409
Okay?

37:17.452 --> 37:18.714
That's you.

37:18.758 --> 37:20.150
I don't --

37:20.194 --> 37:21.804
At a gas station
in Vermont,

37:21.848 --> 37:24.372
minutes before a trucker was
assaulted for his pain pills.

37:24.416 --> 37:26.156
The same pills we found
on Nick Wyndorff

37:26.200 --> 37:28.507
when he was shot
at Allison's house.

37:28.550 --> 37:30.465
The thing is, that video
doesn't mean anything.

37:30.509 --> 37:32.902
And I can't prove it's you.

37:32.946 --> 37:36.732
You were smart. You used cash.
You kept your head down.

37:36.776 --> 37:39.257
But I knowit's you,

37:39.300 --> 37:41.259
and that's got me asking
a lot of questions.

37:41.302 --> 37:43.478
And that's a problem
for you.

37:48.875 --> 37:50.268
I'm sorry.

37:53.227 --> 37:55.316
But...
[Exhales sharply]

37:55.360 --> 37:57.449
...I am not following
any of this.

37:57.492 --> 37:59.755
♪

37:59.799 --> 38:01.148
Neither am I.

38:02.802 --> 38:04.282
But I will.

38:04.325 --> 38:05.935
I mean,
you can tell me now,

38:05.979 --> 38:07.633
and we have a chance of
figuring this out together.

38:07.676 --> 38:10.897
Or I can start
getting answers on my own.

38:10.940 --> 38:14.422
♪

38:14.466 --> 38:17.207
I...

38:17.251 --> 38:20.733
I don't know
what to tell you.

38:20.776 --> 38:21.951
Okay.

38:24.606 --> 38:25.955
Good luck, Patty.

38:25.999 --> 38:32.092
♪

38:32.135 --> 38:36.139
[Door opens, closes]

38:36.183 --> 38:39.404
♪

38:49.152 --> 38:51.329
[Inhales sharply, sighs]

38:51.372 --> 39:00.555
♪

39:00.599 --> 39:09.695
♪

39:09.738 --> 39:11.218
[Exhales sharply, clears throat]

39:11.261 --> 39:19.574
♪

39:19.618 --> 39:22.011
Wake up, sleepyhead!

39:22.055 --> 39:23.404
I'm not sleeping.

39:23.448 --> 39:26.364
Uh, well, maybe you should
'cause you're looking...

39:26.407 --> 39:29.192
lived in.

39:29.236 --> 39:31.238
That's not a compliment.

39:31.281 --> 39:33.414
Well, here.
Drink this.

39:33.458 --> 39:35.721
It'll help you get
some shut-eye.

39:35.764 --> 39:36.939
Oh.

39:36.983 --> 39:39.246
Is this clearance beer
from Deftos?

39:39.289 --> 39:41.727
Yeah.
"Worcester's Pride"!

39:41.770 --> 39:43.816
Oxymoron.

39:43.859 --> 39:46.427
Shame they had to put it on sale
because people in this town

39:46.471 --> 39:49.387
wouldn't support
a local brewery.

39:49.430 --> 39:53.956
They found two human fingers
in one can.

39:54.000 --> 39:56.437
Allison, they already
found two fingers.

39:56.481 --> 39:59.614
How many more could there
possibly be?

39:59.658 --> 40:00.963
Eight.[ Laughter]

40:01.007 --> 40:04.445
Will you just celebrate
with me, please?

40:04.489 --> 40:06.273
Okay. Okay.

40:06.316 --> 40:07.970
Fine.
What are we celebrating?

40:08.014 --> 40:11.670
Well, I took care of my little
Tammy's Gonna Arrest

40:11.713 --> 40:13.628
Me For Arson problem.

40:13.672 --> 40:16.196
You did?
Well, wedid.

40:16.239 --> 40:17.632
And all you have to do

40:17.676 --> 40:20.200
is sign this completely
confidential affidavit

40:20.243 --> 40:22.420
swearing that you saw
her plant evidence

40:22.463 --> 40:24.422
after that guy
broke in here.

40:24.465 --> 40:26.075
And, remember,
you're not telling a lie,

40:26.119 --> 40:30.428
you're just writing
your name near one.

40:30.471 --> 40:33.082
God, we make
such a great team!

40:33.126 --> 40:34.519
[Laughs]

40:36.129 --> 40:37.391
Ah.

40:39.132 --> 40:41.482
Welcome to
the winners' circle.

40:41.526 --> 40:43.876
[Laughs]

40:43.919 --> 40:45.094
Whoo!

40:45.138 --> 40:48.054
[ Laughter]

40:59.935 --> 41:01.284
Oh.

41:04.505 --> 41:13.514
♪

41:13.558 --> 41:22.610
♪

41:22.654 --> 41:24.351
Allison, she knows.

41:24.394 --> 41:25.700
Tammy knows that I was
in Vermont,

41:25.744 --> 41:27.136
she's about to know
everything else.

41:27.180 --> 41:28.486
She was asking
a lot of questions.

41:28.529 --> 41:29.530
She knows that we have
a connection to Nick

41:29.574 --> 41:30.618
and it's all my fault.

41:30.662 --> 41:32.490
I'm so sorry. I'm sorry.

41:32.533 --> 41:35.493
♪

41:45.981 --> 41:47.548
I'll fix it.

41:47.592 --> 41:54.163
♪

41:54.207 --> 42:00.953
♪

42:00.996 --> 42:03.042
[Door closes]

42:08.177 --> 42:11.180
So, when the dentist told me
he'd have to extract the molar,

42:11.224 --> 42:13.356
I looked him square
in the eyes and said,

42:13.400 --> 42:15.533
"You can't
handle the tooth!"

42:16.795 --> 42:18.753
You've told that one before.

42:18.797 --> 42:21.190
I don't get it.

42:21.234 --> 42:22.670
"Tooth"
sounds like "truth."

42:22.714 --> 42:25.717
Oh! Okay.
I still don't get it.

42:25.760 --> 42:27.588
Well, you know
what I don't get?

42:27.632 --> 42:29.242
The fact that you two
just celebrated

42:29.285 --> 42:31.723
your one-month anniversary
by going to Costco

42:31.766 --> 42:32.985
and you didn't bring me back

42:33.028 --> 42:35.770
a single Kirkland
Signature item.

42:35.814 --> 42:39.600
No vitamin water, no batteries,
not even a rotisserie chicken,

42:39.644 --> 42:42.995
which you know
is a loss leader.

42:43.038 --> 42:46.041
And to think I let you
live here.

42:46.085 --> 42:48.217
Well, actually, we've been
discussing that and --

42:48.261 --> 42:50.742
Hey, have you guys
seen Allison?

42:50.785 --> 42:52.439
Yeah. I was just thinking
the same thing.

42:52.482 --> 42:53.614
We got to get Allison
in here --

42:53.658 --> 42:55.268
she always
laughs at my jokes.

42:55.311 --> 42:56.617
Together: Since when?

42:56.661 --> 42:58.619
[ Laughter]

42:58.663 --> 43:00.403
Wait, didn't Allison
say she was going on

43:00.447 --> 43:02.449
one of those fancy walks?

43:02.492 --> 43:04.016
A hike?

43:04.059 --> 43:04.930
A hike!

43:04.973 --> 43:06.584
That was yesterday.

43:06.627 --> 43:08.847
[Knocking]

43:08.890 --> 43:11.023
Hang on!

43:11.066 --> 43:12.938
Ah. Hey, boys.
What's up?

43:12.981 --> 43:15.288
Kev, um...

43:15.331 --> 43:17.812
have you seen your wife
in the last 24 hours?

43:17.856 --> 43:19.771
Um...

43:19.814 --> 43:21.511
No.
No.

43:21.555 --> 43:23.992
Well, Kevin,
this is Allison's.

43:24.036 --> 43:25.820
It was found on
a hiking trail.

43:25.864 --> 43:27.648
We think there's been
an accident.

43:27.692 --> 43:34.176
♪

43:34.220 --> 43:40.792
♪

43:40.835 --> 43:42.620
Where is she?

43:42.663 --> 43:45.666
I don't know.

43:45.710 --> 43:47.450
Not exactly.

43:50.671 --> 43:52.630
But she left something
for you.

43:52.673 --> 43:59.767
♪

43:59.811 --> 44:06.861
♪

44:06.905 --> 44:13.912
♪

44:13.955 --> 44:15.478
Terri: If you end up
wanting the place,

44:15.522 --> 44:18.525
it's first, last,
and security deposit.

44:18.568 --> 44:20.309
Pretty standard.

44:20.353 --> 44:24.923
This area has some of the best
ice fishing in all of Maine.

44:24.966 --> 44:29.101
Last week my husband caught four
lake trout on his first drop.

44:29.144 --> 44:30.842
Mm.

44:30.885 --> 44:34.802
Do you fish,
Ms. Fron...ch -- Fronch?

44:34.846 --> 44:38.110
Um, no, I...

44:38.153 --> 44:39.720
Gertrude's fine.

44:39.764 --> 44:43.071
Well, season's over anyway,
I guess.

44:43.115 --> 44:49.948
♪

44:49.991 --> 44:52.690
So, what do you plan to do
in Danforth?

44:52.733 --> 44:55.344
♪

44:55.388 --> 44:57.129
Sleep.

44:57.172 --> 45:00.132
♪

45:00.175 --> 45:01.524
[Sighs]

45:04.919 --> 45:06.704
♪

45:06.747 --> 45:09.315
Man: Allison.

45:09.358 --> 45:11.578
Allison tried
to kill you.

45:11.621 --> 45:13.058
I'm trying to fix this.

45:13.101 --> 45:15.495
I don't want to know
what you're doing.

45:15.538 --> 45:17.715
This is your best bet
for a new identity.

45:18.977 --> 45:21.196
[Laughing]

45:21.240 --> 45:23.285
Are you an actual idiot?

45:23.329 --> 45:25.113
What?

45:25.157 --> 45:27.725
♪

45:29.770 --> 45:34.166
♪

45:36.037 --> 45:45.786
♪

45:45.830 --> 45:55.622
♪

45:55.665 --> 46:05.414
♪
